                            <comment id="16671606" author="zentol" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 13:20:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test checks whether the client tries to reconnect to the server if it goes down, which requires the server to be restarted on the same port. We could catch &lt;tt&gt;BindExceptions&lt;/tt&gt;  when restarting the server and exit the test early. I don&apos;t see another way to stabilize the test bar form removing it entirely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16672910" author="till.rohrmann" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2018 10:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I think this is a good idea how to harden the test case &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chesnay&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chesnay&quot;&gt;chesnay&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
